This paper deals with the problem of learning optimal reserve price in repeated auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithms introduced in the paper involve online learning and differential privacy, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the analysis of regret, which is a common topic in theoretical computer science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of differential privacy, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR).
